univention-mail-postfix-kolab2 (1.0.6-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * merged from customer trunk: call postmap for /etc/postfix/transport
    even if mail/hosteddomains was unset. Closes Bug #10273
  * merged from customer trunk: added possibility to add additional
    transport map entries via config registry
    mail/maps/transport/<customid>="<transportmap entry>" e.g.
    mail/maps/transport/1="somedomain.org smtp:[mail.somedomain.com]". Closes
    Bug #10274
  * merged from customer trunk:
    + enable sender/recipient canonical maps via config registry

     mail/maps/canonical/sender/enable="<list of enabled map types>"
     mail/maps/canonical/recipient/enable="<list of enabled map types>"

     e.g. mail/maps/canonical/recipient/enable="file ldap"

     currently only "file" and "ldap" are supported

     if "file" is enabled, "/etc/postfix/canonical_sender" resp.
     "/etc/postfix/canonical_recipient" will be used
    + Patch update:
      * specify sender canonical classes via config registry
      mail/maps/canonical/sender/classes="<list of classes>"
      (default: "header_sender")
      * map incoming mail to univentionInternalPrimaryMailAddress instead of
      mailPrimaryAddress if recipient canonical address is enabled

    Closes Bug #10275
  * merged from customer trunk: mail/postfix/dnslookups and
    mail/postfix/softbounce could be set via config registry. Closes Bug
    #10276

